        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer26263433" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14525550226805420377">You have got to love the French! One of their most popular literary characters is a complete psycho. <br/>He kills in cold blood, manipulates everyone around him, sleeps with another man&apos;s wife then kills the man when he objects and spreads terror wherever he goes.<br/>Yet, Fantomas is fascinating and you find yourself worrying when he&apos;s cornered or in danger. His relationship with his mistress has a bit more depth than the usual victorian/turn of the century romances. <br/><br/>Another nice thing is the detective </span>
  <span id="freeText14525550226805420377" style="display:none">You have got to love the French! One of their most popular literary characters is a complete psycho. <br />He kills in cold blood, manipulates everyone around him, sleeps with another man's wife then kills the man when he objects and spreads terror wherever he goes.<br />Yet, Fantomas is fascinating and you find yourself worrying when he's cornered or in danger. His relationship with his mistress has a bit more depth than the usual victorian/turn of the century romances. <br /><br />Another nice thing is the detective that is hunting Fantomas is also an interesting character so you find yourself rooting for both sides.<br />The mysteries are very clever, there's a lot of suspense, adventure and atmosphere.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14525550226805420377" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
